# Paper Enigma

<catsoop-section>Introduction</catsoop-section>

Have you ever thought about how all armies keep their messages secret? Also no one can know about that even if someone conveys the message? There is a tool named **Enigma** which helps us to do this. Enigma was invented by German engineer **Arthur Scherbius** in 1918. Here we will make an enigma using paper.

<catsoop-section>Materials Required</catsoop-section>

- 2 printed A4 sheets
- A cylinder with radius approximately 7.5 cm
- Scissors
- Glue

